org.threadly.litesockets

Class ClientSettableListenableFuture<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.future.SettableListenableFuture<T>
      • org.threadly.litesockets.ClientSettableListenableFuture<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of result returned by this future
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Future<T>, org.threadly.concurrent.future.FutureCallback<T>, org.threadly.concurrent.future.ListenableFuture<T>

    public class ClientSettableListenableFuture<T>
extends org.threadly.concurrent.future.SettableListenableFuture<T>
    Implementation of SettableListenableFuture to access protected constructor where we can specify the executor the listener will complete on. This is very useful / important for litesockets so that optimizations can occur when listeners complete on the client's executor.
